name: sales_amount
text: sale amount of products sold to customers, in currency such as dollars and euros. Ex: we sold $500 of paper last month.

name: quantity
text: quantity of items sold to customers. For example, we sold 40 units of soda.

name: volume
text: gallons or liters or some other unit of volume of products sold to customers

name: pack_size
text: number of items in a pack of some product. Example, lite beer comes in packs of 6, 12, and 24.

name: color
text: color of a product. Example: mugs come in red, blue, or black.

name: gini
text: gini is a metric of the equality across a vector of values. It ranges from 0 through 1, where 0 means it's completely equal.

name: county
text: Administrative division within a state. What items come from my county? What state is this count in?
